041/**
042 * Represents an OpenAPI schema definition.
043 *
044 * <p>
045 * The schema definition can be applied to any HTTP parts such as bodies, headers, query/form parameters, and URL path parts.
046 * <br>The API is generic enough to apply to any path part although some attributes may only applicable for certain parts.
047 *
048 * <p>
049 * Schema objects are created via builders instantiated through the {@link #create()} method.
050 *
051 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
052 *    <li class='note'>This class is thread safe and reusable.
053 * </ul>
054 *
055 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
056 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/OpenApiBasics">OpenAPI Details</a>
057 * </ul>
058 */
059public class HttpPartSchema {

495   /**
496    * Finds the schema information for the specified method parameter.
497    *
498    * <p>
499    * This method will gather all the schema information from the annotations at the following locations:
500    * <ul>
501    *    <li>The method parameter.
502    *    <li>The method parameter class.
503    *    <li>The method parameter parent classes and interfaces.
504    * </ul>
505    *
506    * @param c
507    *    The annotation to look for.
508    *    <br>Valid values:
509    *    <ul>
510    *       <li>{@link Content}
511    *       <li>{@link Header}
512    *       <li>{@link Query}
513    *       <li>{@link FormData}
514    *       <li>{@link Path}
515    *       <li>{@link Response}
516    *       <li>{@link HasQuery}
517    *       <li>{@link HasFormData}
518    *    </ul>
519    * @param mpi The Java method parameter.
520    * @return The schema information about the parameter.
521    */
522   public static HttpPartSchema create(Class<? extends Annotation> c, ParamInfo mpi) {
523      return create().applyAll(c, mpi).build();
524   }
525
526   /**
527    * Finds the schema information for the specified method return.
528    *
529    * <p>
530    * This method will gather all the schema information from the annotations at the following locations:
531    * <ul>
532    *    <li>The method.
533    *    <li>The method return class.
534    *    <li>The method return parent classes and interfaces.
535    * </ul>
536    *
537    * @param c
538    *    The annotation to look for.
539    *    <br>Valid values:
540    *    <ul>
541    *       <li>{@link Content}
542    *       <li>{@link Header}
543    *       <li>{@link Query}
544    *       <li>{@link FormData}
545    *       <li>{@link Path}
546    *       <li>{@link Response}
547    *       <li>{@link HasQuery}
548    *       <li>{@link HasFormData}
549    *    </ul>
550    * @param m
551    *    The Java method with the return type being checked.
552    * @return The schema information about the parameter.
553    */
554   public static HttpPartSchema create(Class<? extends Annotation> c, Method m) {
555      return create().applyAll(c, m).build();
556   }
557
558   /**
559    * Finds the schema information for the specified class.
560    *
561    * <p>
562    * This method will gather all the schema information from the annotations on the class and all parent classes/interfaces.
563    *
564    * @param c
565    *    The annotation to look for.
566    *    <br>Valid values:
567    *    <ul>
568    *       <li>{@link Content}
569    *       <li>{@link Header}
570    *       <li>{@link Query}
571    *       <li>{@link FormData}
572    *       <li>{@link Path}
573    *       <li>{@link Response}
574    *       <li>{@link HasQuery}
575    *       <li>{@link HasFormData}
576    *    </ul>
577    * @param t
578    *    The class containing the parameter.
579    * @return The schema information about the parameter.
580    */
581   public static HttpPartSchema create(Class<? extends Annotation> c, java.lang.reflect.Type t) {
582      return create().applyAll(c, t).build();
583   }

617   /**
618    * Finds the schema information on the specified annotation.
619    *
620    * @param a
621    *    The annotation to find the schema information on..
622    * @param defaultName The default part name if not specified on the annotation.
623    * @return The schema information found on the annotation.
624    */
625   public static HttpPartSchema create(Annotation a, String defaultName) {
626      return create().name(defaultName).apply(a).build();

653      /**
654       * Instantiates a new {@link HttpPartSchema} object based on the configuration of this builder.
655       *
656       * <p>

703       * Apply the specified annotation to this schema.
704       *
705       * @param a The annotation to apply.
706       * @return This object.
707       */
708      public Builder apply(Annotation a) {
709         if (a instanceof Content)
710            apply((Content)a);
711         else if (a instanceof Header)
712            apply((Header)a);
713         else if (a instanceof FormData)
714            apply((FormData)a);
715         else if (a instanceof Query)
716            apply((Query)a);
717         else if (a instanceof Path)
718            apply((Path)a);
719         else if (a instanceof Response)
720            apply((Response)a);
721         else if (a instanceof StatusCode)
722            apply((StatusCode)a);
723         else if (a instanceof HasQuery)
724            apply((HasQuery)a);
725         else if (a instanceof HasFormData)
726            apply((HasFormData)a);
727         else if (a instanceof Schema)
728            apply((Schema)a);
729         else
730            throw new BasicRuntimeException("Builder.apply(@{0}) not defined", className(a));
731         return this;
732      }
